@page "/"

<PageTitle>nuget-systems demos</PageTitle>

<section class="hero-panel">
	<div>
		<p class="eyebrow">Interactive demos</p>
		<h1>Explore nuget-systems through executable examples.</h1>
		<p class="hero-copy">
			The demo host complements the DocFX site with sample inputs and live solver output for the three package families in this repository.
		</p>
	</div>
	<div class="hero-badge-panel">
		<div class="hero-badge">
			<span>3</span>
			<small>demo routes</small>
		</div>
		<div class="hero-badge">
			<span>10+</span>
			<small>solvers touched</small>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>

<section class="section-stack">
	<div class="section-heading">
		<p class="eyebrow">Package map</p>
		<h2>Start from a topic, then inspect the concrete solver output.</h2>
	</div>

	<div class="card-grid card-grid-three">
		<a class="feature-card route-card" href="computing-systems">
			<p class="feature-kicker">Computing systems</p>
			<h3>Binary arithmetic</h3>
			<p>Run binary addition, decimal conversion, and two's-complement scenarios against the concrete computing-solvers package.</p>
		</a>

		<a class="feature-card route-card" href="networking">
			<p class="feature-kicker">Networking</p>
			<h3>Signals and subnetting</h3>
			<p>Inspect line encodings, CRC output, and subnet decomposition with the repository's networking helpers.</p>
		</a>

		<a class="feature-card route-card" href="operating-systems">
			<p class="feature-kicker">Operating systems</p>
			<h3>Page replacement traces</h3>
			<p>Compare FIFO, LRU, Clock, and Optimal replacement behavior step by step using the simulation-backed operating-systems package.</p>
		</a>
	</div>
</section>

<section class="section-stack">
	<div class="section-heading">
		<p class="eyebrow">How it fits</p>
		<h2>DocFX stays the entry point. The demo host adds feedback loops.</h2>
	</div>

	<div class="card-grid card-grid-two">
		<article class="feature-card">
			<p class="feature-kicker">Public docs</p>
			<h3>DocFX site</h3>
			<p>The documentation explains package selection, API surfaces, and topic-to-solver mapping for external consumers.</p>
			<a class="cta-link" href="https://italbytz.github.io/nuget-systems/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Open documentation</a>
		</article>

		<article class="feature-card">
			<p class="feature-kicker">Local feedback</p>
			<h3>Blazor sample app</h3>
			<p>The sample project references the concrete packages directly, so the showcased behavior stays aligned with the code that is actually packed and published.</p>
			<a class="cta-link" href="https://github.com/Italbytz/nuget-systems/tree/main/samples/Italbytz.Systems.Demos.Web" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Inspect sample project</a>
		</article>
	</div>
</section>
